latestIgtvVideos.title: Green up your space
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
#regram • @plantkween DAHLING, the fabulous beginnings of greening up any space starts with a sprinkle of imagination, a dose of that botanical pizazz, and a cute set of those home accessories from my homegurls at @command .... yas, hunny it's springtime, summer's on her way, and this kween is all about that green gurl galore decor! ✨💃🏽🪴
 ⠀
I've always found joy in empty spaces, whether I'm just moving into a new apartment or office, or there's just a random empty wall or corner nook I haven't touched yet.  There is just something about empty space that screams botanical POSSIBILITY and POTENTIAL. As a kween who is about that city living, I've been very intentional about going vertical when it comes to greening up my space, cuz space be a commodity in my lil Brooklyn spot. So I teamed up with @command to highlight a few lil accessories that has been helpful for me in getting the spaces I decorate to serve those luck lewks and viridescent vibes 💁🏽‍♀️🌱🌿🪴
 ⠀
So let’s get into some of my fav @command accessories, dahling: 
 ⠀
🌱 Command Display Ledges - cute for those tiny lil cacti and succulents that you want to have perched right next to the window, so they can soak up that delish sunshine. I've used these ledges for those small lil nook and crannies that could use some lushness 
 ⠀
🌱 Towel Bars: gurl, forget the towels and bring on the green gurls in those hanging planters! Whether it's above your window or on a wall in your bright bathroom these bars have been fun to play with various green gurls who like their vines to trail down, giving that indoor jungle vibe chicness
 ⠀
🌱 Hair Dryer Holder: dahling, more like air plant holder! Our air plant green gurls are epiphytes which means they don't need soil to grow so you best believe this kween is taking advantage of this lil quirky sish and displaying them in all their green glory 
 ⠀
Cheers to that green gurl galore decor, dahling 💃🏽🌱🌿🪴
 ⠀
